1
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:26,480
I feel sorry for you.

2
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,960
Why would you feel sorry for me?

3
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,000
Back then, you were still young.

4
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,240
You probably don't remember

5
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,560
what happened.

6
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:51,240
<i>After Mr. Jinchai married Na,</i>

7
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:56,600
<i>your family looked like</i>
<i>a perfect dream to many people.</i>

8
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:02,160
<i>At that time, Na looked very happy.</i>

9
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:06,440
<i>Mr. Jinchai was a capable man,</i>

10
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:09,800
<i>and Na took good care of the household.</i>

11
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:18,000
<i>Since I was born,</i>

12
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:21,640
<i>I had never seen Na that happy before.</i>

13
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:27,480
<i>That was probably</i>
<i>the happiest time of her life.</i>

14
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,880
<i>Everything was going so well.</i>

15
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:41,520
<i>It felt like that happiness</i>

16
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,080
<i>would last forever.</i>

17
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,800
<i>But then one day,</i>

18
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,920
<i>that woman came into their lives</i>

19
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:55,400
<i>and ruined everything.</i>

20
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,880
<i>Since then,</i>

21
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,640
<i>I've never seen Na smile again.</i>

22
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,000
They took everything away from you.

23
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,040
And you…

24
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,280
I will do anything

25
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,720
to get everything back for you.

26
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,320
Aunt Nong, let me ask you something.

27
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:30,160
What exactly is in that storage room?

28
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,440
Oh? Mr. Warat.

29
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,000
Grandma.

30
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,840
Grandma, did you argue with Warat?

31
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,880
It's nothing.

32
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,360
I just…

33
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,680
I might have made a mistake.

34
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:26,000
What did you do wrong?

35
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,840
Warat has left.

36
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:32,920
Left? Where did he go?

37
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,520
It's my fault

38
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:39,960
for hiding the truth from him all along.

39
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:44,680
What exactly happened, Grandma?

40
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:50,440
<i>This is probably all my fault.</i>

41
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,000
<i>I adopted Praewilai</i>

42
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,840
<i>because her mother died</i>
<i>when she was very young.</i>

43
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:01,520
<i>As for her father, he remarried.</i>

44
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,360
<i>When Prae grew up,</i>

45
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:08,880
<i>she fell in love with Wichan.</i>

46
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:16,160
<i>If they loved each other,</i>
<i>I intended to let them marry.</i>

47
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,800
<i>But…</i>

48
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,480
<i>Ms. Ampha, right?</i>

49
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:29,440
<i>But Wichan fell in love with Ampha,</i>

50
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,760
<i>the secretary I hired.</i>

51
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,480
<i>I didn't want Prae to be heartbroken,</i>

52
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:42,760
<i>so I ordered Wichan to marry Prae.</i>

53
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:47,200
<i>But everything didn't go as I expected.</i>

54
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:54,760
<i>Wichan ended up</i>
<i>registering a marriage with Ampha.</i>

55
00:07:55,640 --> 00:08:00,320
<i>That only made Praewilai</i>
<i>even more devastated.</i>

56
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,160
<i>What did Ms. Prae do then?</i>

57
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:07,160
<i>Praewilai was heartbroken.</i>

58
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,600
<i>She ran away from home.</i>

59
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,440
<i>And when she came back, she was pregnant.</i>

60
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,880
<i>So that means…</i>

61
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:19,480
<i>Warat is not Wichan's son.</i>

62
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,240
<i>When Praewilai returned,</i>

63
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:27,120
<i>she kept repeating</i>

64
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:32,320
<i>that she was sorry</i>
<i>for destroying someone else's family.</i>

65
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:39,120
<i>Family?</i>

66
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,480
<i>Whose family?</i>

67
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,960
<i>Jirasin's.</i>

68
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:49,840
<i>When Jinchai started taking care of</i>
<i>and showing concern for Praewilai,</i>

69
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:53,720
<i>Naree, Jirasin's mother,</i>

70
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,960
<i>fell ill from heartbreak.</i>

71
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:02,400
<i>And in the end, she died of it.</i>

72
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,480
<i>Jinchai died shortly after as well,</i>

73
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:10,520
<i>leaving Jirasin and Lakkana as orphans.</i>

74
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,920
<i>That's why you've been</i>
<i>taking care of Sin like that.</i>

75
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,280
<i>Partly</i>

76
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:29,960
<i>because I wanted Praewilai,</i>
<i>who had already passed away,</i>

77
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:33,000
<i>to rest in peace.</i>

78
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,880
Praewilai didn't want to be a problem,

79
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,680
so she came back
and raised her child quietly.

80
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,200
But…

81
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,840
But what, Grandma?

82
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,360
An accident happened first.

83
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:51,360
Luckily, Ampha was there.

84
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:55,680
So Ampha helped raise the two children,

85
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,880
<i>Waree and Warat.</i>

86
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,240
Waree?

87
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,840
And then suddenly,

88
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,720
Ampha ran away with her people,

89
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:13,880
disappearing with Pong and Soi,

90
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:18,200
and took Waree, my real granddaughter,

91
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:20,160
<i>with her.</i>

92
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,760
<i>Since that day,</i>

93
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:28,720
<i>I've tried to search for them,</i>

94
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:32,720
<i>but no one has ever found</i>
<i>any trace of Ampha</i>

95
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,000
<i>or Waree again.</i>

96
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,240
It's my fault.

97
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,680
I wronged Warat.

98
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:45,080
I wronged everyone.

99
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,880
Grandma,

100
00:10:55,880 --> 00:11:00,000
you already did your best,
to make everyone happy.

101
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,240
I'm so afraid, Boonsita.

102
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,320
I'm afraid that Warat will disappear

103
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,960
and never come back again.

104
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,280
Grandma,

105
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,760
I'll be the one to bring Warat back.

106
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,800
I promise.

107
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,320
Mm. This is good,

108
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:33,760
the project the kids are going to present
to Vanich Mall.

109
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,400
It's good because
you helped guide them, Mom.

110
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:41,040
Mama Toi, Som,

111
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,840
they've sent additional information.

112
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:45,760
Is it anything important?

113
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:53,480
- Arnon…
- Yes.

114
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,080
Then that means that night…

115
00:11:57,760 --> 00:12:00,080
Oh, poor girl.

116
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,880
Both your parents died.

117
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,560
<i>At least it's good you survived.</i>

118
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,560
Let's just hope
it was a normal car accident.

119
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:16,400
If the people in that car
were really Pong and Soi,

120
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,560
then that means…

121
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,640
Ameena.

122
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,360
- Kluay.
- What's wrong?

123
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,280
I…

124
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,640
I came to see Grandma. Is she here?

125
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,120
Mrs. Wanee isn't feeling well.
You can tell me whatever it is.

126
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:01,520
It's something urgent, very important.

127
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,920
I need to see her right now.
Can you help me?

128
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,480
You can tell me first.
I'll pass it on to her.

129
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,760
I…

130
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,480
Can I really tell you?

131
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,360
And if it's about…

132
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:28,080
Let's talk over there.

133
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,680
- Hello, Mr. Warat.
- Well, Jirasin.

134
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,120
Mr. Sarut has been hospitalized, right?

135
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,640
Which hospital is he at?

136
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,600
Are you going to visit Uncle Rut?

137
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:14,840
There's no need. He's not seriously ill.

138
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,880
I have something
I need to talk to him about.

139
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:21,240
You can tell me whatever it is.

140
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:24,280
It's fine. I'll talk to him myself.

141
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:27,760
No need. I'm very close to Uncle Rut.

142
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,600
We talk about everything. Just tell me.

143
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:33,640
Jirasin, shut up and listen to me.

144
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,760
I'm asking which hospital he's in.

145
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:38,240
Just tell me!

146
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,520
Why are you stalling?!

147
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,560
I'm just suggesting the easiest option.

148
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,320
But you refuse.

149
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:49,000
Which hospital is he in, Jirasin?

150
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,920
So what exactly
were you going to tell Grandma?

151
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,040
I…

152
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:23,280
- I…
- You…

153
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,400
I…

154
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:36,360
Well, that night, Warat and I…

155
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,760
- Warat.
- Ameena, let go.

156
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,520
Listen to me first.

157
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:50,520
So you want Mr. Warat
to take responsibility?

158
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,200
Well, I…

159
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,600
Then why do you think it's Mr. Warat?

160
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:08,800
Why not think it could be Det?

161
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:13,320
Well, Det and I…

162
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:16,800
Does Det know? Should I tell him for you?

163
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,120
Or…

164
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,560
does he already know?

165
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:31,560
Well, I…

166
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:34,640
I'm not judging, Ameena, but…

167
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:37,680
if you're saying
this just happened that day,

168
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,080
it's only been a few days.

169
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,600
There's no way
a test would confirm it yet.

170
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:49,360
Before that, Warat and I also…

171
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,520
So this is
what you want to tell Mrs. Wanee?

172
00:16:56,080 --> 00:17:01,880
Kluay, I… I'm sorry. I didn't think
things would turn out like this.

173
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,920
It's okay. I'm not angry. I understand.

174
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,920
We're both women.

175
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,680
We have to protect each other, right?

176
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:18,880
I'm sorry, and thank you
for understanding me.

177
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,079
But Mr. Warat isn't here right now.

178
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,000
He's out of town for work.

179
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:28,640
It's probably another two or three days
before he's back.

180
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:31,680
And if Mrs. Wanee wants to know…

181
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,920
No, I mean,

182
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,400
when she's feeling better, I'll tell her.

183
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,320
I'll tell both of them about this.

184
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:45,760
You're not mad at me, right? I…

185
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,840
Mad about what? Why would I be mad?

186
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:52,640
That I…

187
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:56,560
Well, it's a big deal.

188
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:59,440
No one would lie
about something like this.

189
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:02,120
But if…

190
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:08,040
Well, you're not that kind
of person, right, Ameena?

191
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:11,440
This is serious.
We need to help each other.

192
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,000
Don't overthink it.

193
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,920
How is Uncle Rut? Is he hurt?

194
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,040
He's not seriously injured. Don't worry.

195
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,560
Then should we go visit him?

196
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,200
No need, Aunt Nong.

197
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,440
Someone's already taking care of him.

198
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,600
Who?

199
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,760
His son.

200
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:03,640
- Warat knows already?
- I assume he does.

201
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:06,680
Then our plan…

202
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,200
If he knows,

203
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,040
he'll refuse the inheritance, right?

204
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,040
Don't worry, Aunt Nong.

205
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,840
It's too late to fix anything now.

206
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,960
The fact that Grandma
wanted to open the will,

207
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:23,680
it means everything
has already been finalized.

208
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:25,880
And the reason
Warat stopped the will opening

209
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:29,160
is because
he knows who Uncle Rut really is.

210
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,800
Don't worry.

211
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:34,280
I'll make Grandma proceed with the will.
No matter what, she will.

212
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,920
- And now, Warat isn't here.
- That's even better.

213
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,120
With Warat gone, no one will interfere.

214
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:46,840
And once he accepts it, Uncle Rut
will reveal himself as his father.

215
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,760
And if

216
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,640
Warat happens to have an accident
while inspecting a site…

217
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,680
Anything could happen, right?

218
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,720
Yeah, that's true.

219
00:19:56,800 --> 00:20:00,080
Anything can happen, especially accidents.

220
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:03,640
The legal heir would be his father,

221
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,560
which is Uncle Rut.

222
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,840
Mom.

223
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:21,240
Hello, Anong. They're inside now.

224
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,560
You're watching them
from every angle, right?

225
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:26,160
- Yes.
- <i>Our job is almost done.</i>

226
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,840
Keep watching them closely.

227
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:32,480
The moment they come out,
report to me immediately.

228
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,920
What's wrong, dear?

229
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,560
Why is being an adult so exhausting, Mom?

230
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,880
Come here. Who upset you this time?

231
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,880
Ameena came and said

232
00:21:57,600 --> 00:22:00,160
Mr. Warat got her pregnant.

233
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,600
And what did he say?

234
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:07,400
He disappeared.

235
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,640
I tried calling him, but he won't pick up.

236
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:14,960
Well, if you haven't heard
the truth from him yet,

237
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,640
there's no need to overthink.

238
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:20,880
You already know what Ameena is like.

239
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:28,520
But what if Mr. Warat cheated on me?

240
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:32,120
Don't jump to conclusions
before anything is confirmed.

241
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:35,760
- But Ameena said--
- If I were you,

242
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:39,040
I would choose to trust my partner.

243
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:42,760
Talk to both of them in person.

244
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,760
Then you'll know the truth.

245
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:48,840
As long as
you haven't heard it from Mr. Warat,

246
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:50,840
don't overthink it.

247
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:54,320
Suspicion won't help anything.

248
00:22:56,360 --> 00:23:01,800
And what if the truth
turns out like what Ameena said?

249
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:06,840
If it's true,

250
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:12,440
then you don't need to care
about someone who isn't loyal to you.

251
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:16,680
You haven't lost anything.

252
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:27,600
Thank you, Mom,
for bringing me back to my senses.

253
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,560
Of course.

254
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,080
You've already done so well,

255
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,360
enduring all this.

256
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,880
And where did Mr. Warat go?

257
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:42,760
Oh.

258
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:50,120
Actually, that's another reason
why I'm not that angry at him.

259
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,920
Why?

260
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,440
He's probably dealing
with something big right now.

261
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,800
Talk it out calmly.

262
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:08,000
There's always a solution.

263
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,720
Yes, Mom.

264
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:16,160
Come here, my good girl.

265
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:19,520
- Thank you.
- Mm.

266
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,960
What should we do with him?

267
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:29,440
He's another one we need to settle with.

268
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:31,320
If we're going to act, it has to be now,

269
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,560
before he exposes us.

270
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:36,280
I'll handle it.

271
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,840
And we don't know where he is.

272
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:41,360
If we want our plan to be complete,

273
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:43,680
we'll have to get rid of Kluay too.

274
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:47,040
What does she have to do with anything?

275
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:50,480
Everything, of course.

276
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,240
Because I believe

277
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:56,560
Kluay is actually the real granddaughter
of the Vanich family.

278
00:24:58,640 --> 00:24:59,920
What do you mean?

279
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,120
I think Kluay is Waree.

280
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,480
Waree?

281
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:11,160
Waree, the only heir of the Vanich family.

282
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:15,720
Does anyone else know about this?

283
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,280
They don't know about this yet.

284
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:25,280
And this secret will die along with Kluay.

285
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,640
What do you mean?

286
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:52,240
Kluay, where are you going?

287
00:25:57,760 --> 00:26:00,120
I'm going to find Mr. Warat.

288
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:03,800
Do you even know where he is?

289
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,760
I have my ways.

290
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:10,040
No. If you're going, I'm going too.

291
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:15,280
You can't. I have something important
to talk to him about.

292
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:19,360
Then just talk to him, I won't interfere.

293
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:22,960
It's really fine. It's just…

294
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,720
Just what?

295
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,880
You don't even know where he is.

296
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:29,160
I'm just worried--

297
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,960
Then if we go, we all go together.

298
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:38,440
Fine. Then I won't go.

299
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:48,440
Hello, Anong.

300
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:51,720
It looks like she just came out.
But someone took her back inside.

301
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,480
Good. Keep an eye on her.
Don't lose sight of her.

302
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:59,160
If she comes out again,
follow her immediately.

303
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:01,360
<i>Yes, alright. And about…</i>

304
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:04,600
Don't worry about the money.

305
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:07,880
Once this is done, you'll be set for life.

306
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,680
Mr. Warat?

307
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,840
I heard from Jirasin that you're sick.

308
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,040
Are you okay?

309
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,920
It's nothing serious.

310
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,120
I should be discharged soon.

311
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,000
- Mr. Sarut.
- Yes?

312
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,480
Can I ask you something?

313
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,840
Of course.

314
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,080
You've always known…

315
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:30,960
that you're my father, right?

316
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:48,400
Warat, calm down.

317
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:52,080
Please, calm down.

318
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,600
Can I ask you something?

319
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:59,720
Why did you do that to me?

320
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:04,160
At that time,

321
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,640
it was the best thing…

322
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:13,320
I could do for you.

323
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:23,320
What really happened?

324
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:27,840
Back then…

325
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:31,000
Prae… Prae is dead…

326
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,280
What am I supposed to do? And my child.

327
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:39,720
Calm down.

328
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:43,000
We'll fix this step by step.

329
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:47,120
But no matter what,
I have to bring Warat back.

330
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,880
You're just going to walk

331
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:54,240
into the Vanich family
and tell them you're his father?

332
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:57,320
Do you think Mrs. Wanee
would just hand him over to you?

333
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,960
No matter what, I have to bring him back.

334
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:05,200
He's my son. I can't abandon him.

335
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:08,400
Calm down. Well,

336
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:13,000
I don't agree with bringing him back.

337
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,200
Why not?

338
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,040
He's my son. What do you expect me to do?

339
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,720
Abandon him? I won't.

340
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,360
- Calm down.
- I…

341
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:23,920
No, you don't have to abandon him.

342
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:33,280
Just let him
stay there and fulfill his role.

343
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:38,440
Role? What role?

344
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,480
Mr. Rut, think carefully.

345
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:45,120
Would Mr. Warat be better off

346
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:47,800
living with the Vanich family

347
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,640
or with you?

348
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,240
But still,

349
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:04,400
I have to bring him back.

350
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,280
I won't leave my child.

351
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:10,120
If you let him stay there

352
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:13,440
and inherit the Vanich fortune,

353
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:16,080
just think about it,

354
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:19,520
you and Warat will be set for life.

355
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:24,480
<i>You just need to have</i>
<i>your workers, Pong and Soi,</i>

356
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:28,640
<i>bring Ampha and the child Waree out.</i>

357
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,600
<i>And how are you going to</i>
<i>separate Ampha from Wichan?</i>

358
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:35,640
<i>Create an emergency.</i>

359
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,120
<i>Something serious.</i>

360
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,720
<i>What? Aunt Noi got hit by a car?</i>

361
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:50,560
Pong, Soi,
this isn't the way to the hospital.

362
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,400
Where are you taking us?

363
00:31:57,360 --> 00:31:58,560
<i>Back then,</i>

364
00:31:58,640 --> 00:32:01,120
I just wanted to ask Ampha

365
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:04,000
to take care of you like her own child.

366
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:13,960
You had no right to do that.

367
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:16,480
No right at all.

368
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:19,880
I had nothing to do with Ampha's death.

369
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:22,160
You killed her!

370
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,800
I didn't.

371
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:29,000
I didn't kill her. I did it for you.

372
00:32:33,120 --> 00:32:34,920
From now on,

373
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,640
don't do anything for me anymore.

374
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:41,000
Don't do anything for me.

375
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:44,440
Calm down, son.

376
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,840
- My son.
- Don't call me that.

377
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,640
You've never been my father.

378
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:53,400
My only father was Mr. Wichan.

379
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,440
My son. My son!

380
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:59,120
Listen to me, my son.

381
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,400
There's a thief in the house!

382
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,480
Where? Som, be careful!

383
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:36,720
Just kidding.

384
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:42,080
- What's wrong?
- Som.

385
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:45,600
Don't joke like that. You scared me.

386
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:48,120
I'm on watch.

387
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:51,080
On watch? You were sleeping.

388
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:52,840
You were about to start snoring.

389
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:55,880
If you're sleepy, go sleep.

390
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:58,960
There are guards at every entrance.
Don't worry.

391
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:02,480
No way.
Too many things are happening here.

392
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:06,240
So are you going to tell me now?

393
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:08,560
The jewelry you're looking for,

394
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:10,000
who is it for?

395
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,199
Mr. Warat.

396
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:16,400
Mr. Warat.

397
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:19,560
- Mr. Warat asked me to find it.
- Oh…

398
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:21,719
Mm. Can I even believe that?

399
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:23,199
It's true.

400
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,880
I have something for you too.

401
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:33,880
What is it?

402
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:38,719
This pendant will help ward off
evil spirits and bad luck

403
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:40,920
from your boyfriend.

404
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,760
That's not real.

405
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,320
Who would believe that?

406
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:46,760
- Just carry it with you.
- Mm.

407
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:50,400
It'll protect you and keep you safe

408
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,760
from anything bad that comes near you.

409
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:57,040
Som, how old are you?
You still believe in stuff like this?

410
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:59,480
Hey, I'm just worried about you.

411
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:02,680
You just said yourself
there's been a lot going on lately.

412
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:05,880
- Fine, if you don't want it, I'll keep it.
- Alright, alright.

413
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:08,320
Better safe than sorry.

414
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,000
Give me your wallet.

415
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:16,600
Here, keep it in your wallet.

416
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:20,640
It'll protect you from danger
and from anyone with bad intentions.

417
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:21,920
Let it be!

418
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,000
This is good stuff, you know.

419
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:26,040
Really?

420
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,640
Keep it. Don't take it out.

421
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,280
Did you need something, Mom?

422
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:53,680
Did Warat call you?

423
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:57,160
Yes. Did something happen to him?

424
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,640
Did he ask you anything?

425
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,880
He asked about Uncle Rut.
He said he had business with him.

426
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,640
Where is Sarut now?

427
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:08,800
At the hospital.

428
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:10,840
Should I call and ask Warat to come back?

429
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:11,880
No.

430
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:15,760
He won't come back.

431
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:19,280
If he won't come back,
then make him come back.

432
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,520
How?

433
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,800
Announce the will.

434
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,880
Whether he accepts it or not,

435
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,520
he'll have to come back.

436
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:06,080
Mrs. Wanee announced the will.

437
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,840
Even without Mr. Warat?

438
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:13,240
MRS. WANEE VANICH

439
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:16,920
Just as expected.

440
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,040
Mr. Warat

441
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:23,720
has been appointed to take over
all of Vanich's business.

442
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:27,400
As for the other relatives,
they've been given land.

443
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:32,680
- But wait.
- What is it?

444
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:34,920
Jirasin…

445
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:40,560
also received shares in Vanich Mall.

446
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:51,000
I don't know how to repay you…

447
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,280
NEXT EPISODE

448
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:53,400
…Grandma.

449
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:59,280
Just repay me by fulfilling the duty
you're supposed to do.

450
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:04,080
Go finish what we started.

451
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:07,280
Mr. Warat has been kidnapped.

452
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:11,400
Mr. Warat, I… I'm here now.

453
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:13,760
Mr. Warat's not here. Let's go.

454
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:16,440
He is. He's here.

455
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:19,840
Kluay!

456
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:20,960
Kluay.

457
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:52,840
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
